# Expat Atlas — Cursor Rules

Read `AGENTS.md` and planning docs before substantive changes.

## Product
- Expat transition OS, not a travel blog
- Every page answers: "What do I do next?"
- Build house now, furniture later — full structure, no fake partnerships

## Trust (non-negotiable)
- No legal/immigration/tax advice as final authority
- No fake verified partners, sponsors, or attorneys
- Label demo data, affiliates, sponsored placements
- Source claims require metadata or `needs_review` state

## Stack
- Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn, Supabase, Drizzle
- Monorepo: apps/web, packages/*
- Follow `ROADMAP.md` phase order

## Code
- Minimize scope; match existing conventions
- Shared logic in packages (not duplicated in web/mobile)
- Lazy-load Three.js and heavy animations
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Skills
- Use GStack for plan/review/qa/ship at phase boundaries
- Design: frontend-design, theme-factory, scroll-experience, threejs-interaction
- DB: supabase-postgres-best-practices
- QA: playwright-best-practices, webapp-testing
